{# FAQ #}
<section class="py-12">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
    <h2 class="section-heading mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <details class="card p-5 group" open>
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
          What is the 30% ruling in the Netherlands?
          <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform"></i>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          The 30% ruling is a Dutch tax advantage for skilled migrants recruited from abroad. It allows employers to pay 30% of the employee's salary as a tax-free allowance for up to five years. To qualify, you must be recruited from at least 150 km outside the Dutch border and meet minimum salary thresholds. This effectively increases your net income significantly.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details class="card p-5 group">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
          Do I need to speak Dutch to work in tech?
          <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform"></i>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          No. The Netherlands has one of the highest English proficiency rates in the world for non-native speakers. Nearly all tech companies use English as their working language. While learning Dutch is appreciated and helpful for social integration, it's not required for most tech positions.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details class="card p-5 group">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
          What visa do I need to work in the Netherlands?
          <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform"></i>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Most tech professionals use the <strong>Highly Skilled Migrant (Kennismigrant)</strong> visa. Your employer must be a recognized sponsor with the Dutch immigration service (IND). The process is typically fast — approval often takes 2–4 weeks. Salary thresholds apply (reduced for those under 30). All companies listed on this page provide visa sponsorship.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details class="card p-5 group">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
          What's the cost of living in Amsterdam?
          <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform"></i>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Amsterdam is one of the more expensive cities in the Netherlands. Expect to pay €1,500–€2,200/month for a one-bedroom apartment in the city center. However, cities like Rotterdam, Eindhoven, and Utrecht offer lower rents with excellent connectivity. The 30% ruling helps offset costs considerably. Use our <a href="/tools/cost-of-living/" class="text-brand-600 dark:text-brand-400 hover:underline">Cost of Living Calculator</a> for detailed comparisons.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

